  ABOUT COOPTINYTEAM

  CoOpTinyTeam is a brand, concept, and project created and owned by
  Oleksii Povolotskyi (a.povolotskiy@gmail.com). The name, idea, and any
  company or entity operating under the CoOpTinyTeam identity belong
  exclusively to Oleksii Povolotskyi. All rights not expressly granted
  below are reserved.

  CoOp Tiny Team is an open-invitation arcade platform — anyone can play,
  share, and build games for it. The rules below are designed to protect
  the platform and the brand while giving contributors real, meaningful
  credit for the games they create.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

1. OWNERSHIP

   1.1  The CoOpTinyTeam brand, concept, and any associated company or
        legal entity are the exclusive property of Oleksii Povolotskyi
        ("the Owner"). This includes the original idea for the platform,
        the CoOp Tiny Team name, logo, and all derivative branding.

   1.2  The platform source code, assets, documentation, and all
        associated materials ("the Platform") are owned by CoOpTinyTeam,
        a project of Oleksii Povolotskyi.

   1.3  Each individual game contributed to the platform ("a Game") is
        co-owned as follows:

        — The game's original author(s) ("the Game Author") retain
          authorship credit and are named as the game's creator in the
          platform UI, documentation, and any release materials.

        — CoOpTinyTeam (and thereby Oleksii Povolotskyi) holds all
          intellectual-property and commercialisation rights to the Game
          as part of the CoOp Tiny Team Arcade catalogue. This allows the
          platform to remain coherent and sustainable.

   1.4  No contributor acquires ownership of the Platform, the CoOpTinyTeam
        brand, or any associated company or business entity.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

2. WHAT EVERYONE CAN DO (FREE OF CHARGE)

   ✔  Play any game on the platform in a browser, at any time, for free.
   ✔  Share the platform URL or a link to any specific game with anyone.
   ✔  Stream, record, or post gameplay footage, with attribution
      ("CoOp Tiny Team by Oleksii Povolotskyi").
   ✔  Read and study the source code for personal learning.
   ✔  Fork the repository to experiment locally on your own machine.
   ✔  Contribute new games or improvements (see Section 4).

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

3. WHAT IS NOT PERMITTED

   Unless you have prior written permission from the Owner, you may NOT:

   ✗  Redistribute, publish, or host a copy of the Platform or any Game
      (modified or unmodified) on a domain or service you control.

   ✗  Use the Platform, any Game, or any substantial portion of the source
      code in a commercial product, SaaS offering, or paid service.

   ✗  Remove, replace, or obscure any copyright notice, author credit,
      or "CoOp Tiny Team" attribution from any part of the Platform.

   ✗  Sell, sublicense, or transfer any part of this software to a
      third party.

   ✗  Claim ownership of a contributed Game independent of the platform.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

4. CONTRIBUTOR TERMS — BUILDING A GAME

   By submitting a pull request that adds or modifies a Game you agree:

   4.1  AUTHORSHIP CREDIT
        Your name (or team name) will be displayed as the Game Author in
        the platform UI. This credit is permanent and survives future
        changes to the codebase.

   4.2  LICENCE GRANT
        You grant the Owner a perpetual, worldwide, irrevocable,
        royalty-free right to use, modify, publish, and commercially
        exploit your Game as part of the CoOp Tiny Team Arcade catalogue.

   4.3  IP ASSIGNMENT
        All intellectual-property rights in the contributed Game vest in
        and are assigned to the Owner upon acceptance of the contribution,
        subject to the authorship credit in 4.1.

   4.4  ORIGINALITY
        You represent that your contribution is original work, does not
        infringe any third-party rights, and that you have the authority
        to make the above grant.

   4.5  NO OBLIGATION
        The Owner is under no obligation to accept, publish, or maintain
        any contribution.

